{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:proverbs.30",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "proverbs",
    "chapterNumber": 30,
    "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30",
    "summary": "Source text for Proverbs 30 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.30.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:1",
      "text": "The words of Agur son of Jakeh of Massa. The man says to Ithi-el, to Ithi-el and Ucal:",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.30.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:2",
      "text": "Surely I am too stupid to be a man. I have not the understanding of a man.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.30.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:3",
      "text": "I have not learned wisdom, nor have I knowledge of the Holy One.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.30.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:4",
      "text": "Who has ascended to heaven and come down? Who has gathered the wind in his fists? Who has wrapped up the waters in a garment? Who has established all the ends of the earth? What is his name, and what is his son's name? Surely you know!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.30.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:5",
      "text": "Every word of God proves true; he is a shield to those who take refuge in him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.30.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:6",
      "text": "Do not add to his words, lest he rebuke you, and you be found a liar.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.30.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:7",
      "text": "Two things I ask of thee; deny them not to me before I die:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.30.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:8",
      "text": "Remove far from me falsehood and lying; give me neither poverty nor riches; feed me with the food that is needful for me,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.30.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:9",
      "text": "lest I be full, and deny thee, and say, “Who is the Lord?” or lest I be poor, and steal, and profane the name of my God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.30.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:10",
      "text": "Do not slander a servant to his master, lest he curse you, and you be held guilty.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.30.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:11",
      "text": "There are those who curse their fathers and do not bless their mothers.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.30.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:12",
      "text": "There are those who are pure in their own eyes but are not cleansed of their filth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.30.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:13",
      "text": "There are those—how lofty are their eyes, how high their eyelids lift!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.30.14",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:14",
      "text": "There are those whose teeth are swords, whose teeth are knives, to devour the poor from off the earth, the needy from among men.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.30.15",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:15",
      "text": "The leech has two daughters; “Give, give,” they cry. Three things are never satisfied; four never say, “Enough”:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.30.16",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:16",
      "text": "Sheol, the barren womb, the earth ever thirsty for water, and the fire which never says, “Enough.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.30.17",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:17",
      "text": "The eye that mocks a father and scorns to obey a mother will be picked out by the ravens of the valley and eaten by the vultures.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.30.18",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:18",
      "text": "Three things are too wonderful for me; four I do not understand:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.30.19",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:19",
      "text": "the way of an eagle in the sky, the way of a serpent on a rock, the way of a ship on the high seas, and the way of a man with a maiden.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.30.20",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:20",
      "text": "This is the way of an adulteress: she eats, and wipes her mouth, and says, “I have done no wrong.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.30.21",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:21",
      "text": "Under three things the earth trembles; under four it cannot bear up:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.30.22",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:22",
      "text": "a slave when he becomes king, and a fool when he is filled with food;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.30.23",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:23",
      "text": "an unloved woman when she gets a husband, and a maid when she succeeds her mistress.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.30.24",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:24",
      "text": "Four things on earth are small, but they are exceedingly wise:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.30.25",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:25",
      "text": "the ants are a people not strong, yet they provide their food in the summer;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.30.26",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:26",
      "text": "the badgers are a people not mighty, yet they make their homes in the rocks;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.30.27",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:27",
      "text": "the locusts have no king, yet all of them march in rank;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.30.28",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:28",
      "text": "the lizard you can take in your hands, yet it is in kings' palaces.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.30.29",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:29",
      "text": "Three things are stately in their tread; four are stately in their stride:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.30.30",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:30",
      "text": "the lion, which is mightiest among beasts and does not turn back before any;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.30.31",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:31",
      "text": "the strutting cock, the he-goat, and a king striding before his people.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.30.32",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:32",
      "text": "If you have been foolish, exalting yourself, or if you have been devising evil, put your hand on your mouth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.30.33",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 30,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 30:33",
      "text": "For pressing milk produces curds, pressing the nose produces blood, and pressing anger produces strife.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
